I'm in a contemplative mood.  there's a lot to think about. some good, some....well not so good. i went back and read some old entries in my journal (my real journal not this thing) and it makes me feel like such a drama queen. i've gotta a lot of mixed emotions working here. so many things i need to make decisions about. paths i would like to walk down again because i've become addicted to the journey but i know the destination oh so well, in the end i will feel like an idiot, i will feel completely stupid for doing something when i knew how it would be in the end. but i'm so tempted. i just wanna go back to one of those days, one when i felt so...untouchable. like i could acheive this beautiful day when it was just like it used to be. i KNOW i don't really want it like it used to be. but wouldnt that be nice? rrrrr... i need to make up my mind. i need to know exactly how i feel before i'm put in a situation when that feeling needs to act. i really don't know what i want any more. just some one to hold me i guess. to feel like its alright, you know? just to be told that everthing will be fine, and be so comforted you don't care if you know its not true...yes, that would be nice
~sigh~ Todays a bad day and I get the feeling it's going to be a bad week. I need to cuddle or something. I love the comfort you find in some ones arms, and I wish i could just have that comfort now.
i want...cake...and ice cream. or a cookie of course

i came to a incredibly depressing relization just a few moments ago. 
i dont know what has happened. what happened to how it was. its been so long since i've had a conversation like i used to have all the time. so long since i've had a really deep conversation thats a little weird and doesnt exactly make sense but one that i wont forget. like the conversation katie and i once had about stars and eyes and just all this shit where we got so symbolic with every thing. its like the things you think but dont say because you dont always know how. i used to have such amazing conversations with people and i just dont have conversations like that any more. dont get me wrong cause i do love conversations that i have (like with you sam) but its not the same. guys or girls or petty arguments are subjects of so many of my conversations. i've had a lot of coversations about absolutly nothing!!! that used to be one of the biggest annoyances to me. such small talk. why? what has changed so much that i dont do what was once one of my favorite things in the world. what happend to my conversations? is it that i dont talk to the people i used to? is it that katie and i have so much going on that we are no longer apart of? we used to talk forever before she left. i'm close to tears thinking that maybe i won't have a conversation like that with all the new friends i have these days. so much has changed in my life. i remember when i hardly lived in this world. when i walked in dreams and books and i tried so very hard just to escape reality it seems. i dont sketch in my sketch book as often as i did. i cant remeber all my dreams like i used to. i dont...understand where i turned so sharp. i dont write poetry like i used to. i dont cut out eyes from magazines any more. i dont know what happened to my lyric book. i havent gone out into the woods alone in so long. i havent gone out of my way to watch the sun set in so long i cant remember the last time i did! i've changed so much, some are good changes, but these are bad...no...these scare me. these help me flinch at my reflection at night. i dont recognize myself like i once did. i dont get lost in my imagination like i used to. please dont tell me that this is getting older!! please dont tell me this is me growing up!!!! i wanna go back when i could get lost in a book for hours on end and write pages and pages of nonsense i wanna talk to somebody and afterwards feel like ive uncovered secrets about life!!!!!!! i want a really conversation...
